xk1x0,1

findruns1 <- function(x, k) {
  n <- length(x)
  runs <- NULL
  for(i in 1:(n-k+1)) {
    if(all(x[i:(i+k-1)] == 1)) runs <- c(runs, i)
  }
  return(runs)
}
findruns1(c(1,0,0,1,1,1,0,1,1),2)
## [1] 4 5 8

findruns

findruns2 <- function(x, k) {
  n <- length(x)
  runs <- vector(length = n)
  count <- 0
  for(i in 1:(n-k+1)) {
    if(all(x[i:(i+k-1)] == 1)) {
      count <- count + 1
      runs[count] <- i
    }
  }
  
  if(count > 0) {
    runs <- runs[1:count]
  } else {
    runs <- NULL
  }
  return(runs)
}

allall

findruns3 <- function(x, k) {
  n <- length(x)
  runs <- vector(length = n)
  count <- 0
  i <- 1
  for(j in 1:n) {
    if(x[j] == 1) {
      if((j-i) == (k-1)){
        count <- count + 1
        runs[count] <- i
        i <- i + 1
      } 
    } else {
      i <- j + 1   # i
    }
  }
  
  if(count > 0) {
    runs <- runs[1:count]
  } else {
    runs <- NULL
  }
  return(runs)
}
# test case
x <- c(1, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 1, 1)
for(k in 1:length(x)) {
  if(all(findruns1(x, k) == findruns3(x, k))) {

    print("something wrong!!")
  }
}

preda1 <- function(x, k) {
  n <- length(x)
  k2 <- k / 2
  pred <- vector(length = n-k)
  for(i in 1:(n-k)) {
    if(sum(x[i:(i+(k-1))]) >= k2) pred[i] <- 1 else pred[i] <- 0
  }
  return(mean(abs(pred - x[(k+1):n])))
}

sum

pred2 <- function(x, k) {
  n <- length(x)
  k2 <- k / 2
  pred <- vector(length = n-k)
  sm <- sum(x[1:k])
  for(i in 1:(n-k)){
    if(sm >= k2) {
      pred[i] <- 1 
    } else {
      pred[i] <- 0
    }
    sm <- sm - x[i] + x[i+k]
  }
  return(mean(abs(pred - x[(k+1):n])))
}
####      
predb <- function(x,k) {
  n <- length(x)
  k2 <- k/2
  pred <- vector(length=n-k)
  sm <- sum(x[1:k])
  
  if (sm >= k2) pred[1] <- 1 else pred[1] <- 0 
  if (n-k>=2){
    for (i in 2:(n-k)) {
      sm <- sm + x[i+k-1] - x[i-1]
      if (sm >= k2) pred[i] <- 1 else pred[i] <- 0
    }
  }
  return(mean(abs(pred-x[(k+1):n])))
}

pred3 <- function(x, k) {
  n <- length(x)
  k2 <- k/2
  pred <- vector(length=n-k)
  csx <- c(0, cumsum(x))  # !!
  for(i in 1:(n-k)){
    if((csx[i+k]-csx[i]) >= k2) pred[i] <- 1 else pred[i] <- 0
  }
  return(mean(abs(pred-x[(k+1):n])))
}

example2

# 11
findud <- function(v) {
  vud <- v[-1] - v[-length(v)]
  return(ifelse(vud > 0, 1, -1))
}

udcorr <- function(x, y) {
  ud <- lapply(list(x, y), findud)
  return(mean(ud[[1]] == ud[[2]]))
}

x <- c(1, 3, 2, 5, 4)
y <- c(3, 1, 2, 5, 4)
udcorr(x, y)
## [1] 0.5
lapply(list(x, y), findud)
## [[1]]
## [1]  1 -1  1 -1
## 
## [[2]]
## [1] -1  1  1 -1
